Huadian Plans Four Dams to Boost Hydro Generation Capacity, Daily Reports

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-05-10T01:06:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/huadian-plans-four-dams-to-boost-hydro-generation-capacity-daily-reports.html
China  Huadian Corp. plans to build
four new hydropower stations along rivers in southern China to
boost its hydro-generating capacity by 63 percent over the next
five years, the  China Daily  reported.  The parent company of Hong Kong-listed Huadian Power
International Corp. plans to develop 10 gigawatts of additional
hydroelectric capacity through 2015, the newspaper reported,
citing company spokesman, Yuan Minggang. China Huadian aims to
have 26 gigawatts of hydropower capacity by 2015, or 8 percent
of the nationâ€™s total by then, it said.  To contact the Bloomberg News staff on this story
